            <title>[OAK-4195] Use clock when waiting in ClusterNodeInfo</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-4195</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ClusterNodeInfo currently uses a Thread.sleep() when it waits for a lease to end in waitForLeaseExpiry(). The method should rather use clock.waitUntil() to make use of a potential virtual clock in use by a test. This allows to reduce the time it takes to run lease related tests.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
